---
import { Plus } from 'lucide-react';
---

<section id="faq" class="w-full px-4 sm:px-8 py-16 lg:py-32 bg-surface brutal-border-b relative z-10 overflow-hidden">
	<!-- Optional grid background for the 'Intel' theme -->
	<div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle,black_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:20px_20px] opacity-5 pointer-events-none"></div>

	<div class="max-w-[1000px] mx-auto observe-block relative z-10">
		<div class="text-center mb-12 lg:mb-24">
			<span class="inline-block bg-black text-white px-4 py-2 text-[14px] font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border-4 border-black shadow-[4px_4px_0_0_#16A34A] transform rotate-2 mb-6">
				[ 06. Intel Briefing ]
			</span>
			<h2 class="text-[42px] sm:text-[50px] md:text-[80px] font-black uppercase leading-[0.9] mt-4">
				<span class="reveal-overflow"><span class="reveal-text block">Common</span></span>
				<span class="reveal-overflow"><span class="reveal-text block text-transparent" style="-webkit-text-stroke: 2px black;">Questions</span></span>
			</h2>
		</div>

		<div class="flex flex-col gap-12 lg:gap-16">
			
			<!-- 💰 Investment & Process -->
			<div class="stamp-item delay-100 relative">
				<div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-warning text-black px-4 py-2 text-[14px] font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border-2 border-black shadow-[3px_3px_0_0_#000] mb-6 transform -rotate-1 relative z-20 -ml-2 sm:ml-0">
					<span class="text-[18px]">💰</span> Investment & Process
				</div>
				
				<div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">How much does a website usually cost?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							The cost depends on your business goals. For a complete custom modernization, projects typically start around $5,000+. If you have an existing site that just needs technical rescuing (speed fixes, broken layouts), those projects start around $750. If a large upfront cost is a barrier, I also offer a "Website as a Service" (WaaS) model where you pay a low monthly subscription with $0 upfront.
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">What is "Website as a Service" (WaaS)?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							Think of it like leasing a high-performance vehicle. Instead of paying $5,000+ upfront, you pay a flat monthly fee (typically around $150–$350/mo). This includes custom design, ultra-fast hosting, daily backups, security monitoring, and unlimited minor content edits. It allows you to get a premium website while preserving your cash flow.
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">How long does a project take?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							Most custom modernization or new builds take between 3 to 6 weeks. Performance rescues or WaaS setups can often be launched much faster. My goal is to get your new "operational hub" live quickly so you can start seeing a return on investment (ROI).
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- 🚀 Performance & UX -->
			<div class="stamp-item delay-200 relative">
				<div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-[#3B82F6] text-white px-4 py-2 text-[14px] font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border-2 border-black shadow-[3px_3px_0_0_#000] mb-6 transform rotate-1 relative z-20 -ml-2 sm:ml-0">
					<span class="text-[18px]">🚀</span> Performance & UX
				</div>
				
				<div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">Why custom development instead of Wix or Squarespace?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							DIY builders are great for hobbyists, but they often suffer from slow load times and limited SEO capabilities as your business grows. In 2025, a 1-second delay in page load time can cut your conversions by 7%, and 53% of mobile users will abandon a site that takes longer than 3 seconds to load. I build custom, lightning-fast websites (often using modern frameworks like Astro or Next.js) that load in under 1 second, directly increasing your sales and leads.
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">Do you work with WordPress, or can you fix my existing site?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							Yes. Many of my clients come to me with bloated WordPress themes, plugin conflicts, or terrible mobile layouts. I can audit your current setup and do a "Performance Recovery" to repair it without starting from scratch. If your WordPress site is beyond repair, I can migrate you to a faster, modern architecture (like Headless WordPress or Astro) for ultimate speed and security.
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">Will this site work well on mobile?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							Absolutely. In 2025, over 60% of all website traffic comes from mobile devices. More importantly, 57% of users say they will not recommend a business if its mobile website is poorly designed or hard to use. I design every project with a "Mobile-First" approach, ensuring the interface is "thumb-friendly" and loads instantly. Since Google now uses mobile-first indexing as the standard, a flawless mobile experience directly improves your search engine rankings and keeps local customers engaged.
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- 🛡️ Security, SEO & AI -->
			<div class="stamp-item delay-300 relative">
				<div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-[#EF4444] text-white px-4 py-2 text-[14px] font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-widest border-2 border-black shadow-[3px_3px_0_0_#000] mb-6 transform -rotate-2 relative z-20 -ml-2 sm:ml-0">
					<span class="text-[18px]">🛡️</span> Security, SEO & AI
				</div>
				
				<div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">Can you help with SEO?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							Yes. All my builds are technically optimized for search engines by default. I focus heavily on Core Web Vitals (speed, interactivity, visual stability)—metrics that Google now uses to rank websites. A fast, mobile-friendly site is the foundation of modern SEO. I also offer ongoing technical SEO strategy to improve your rankings over time.
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">Why do I need ongoing support/maintenance?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							Over 43% of cyberattacks target small businesses, often exploiting outdated plugins or fragile code. My monthly retention packages keep your site updated, secure, and running at peak performance. This means zero downtime for your business, and you never have to worry about your site breaking in the middle of a busy sales day.
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">How do you ensure my site is secure?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							It’s a valid concern—today, 43% of cyberattacks specifically target small businesses. Many businesses use outdated platforms like WordPress, which are highly vulnerable to plugin exploits; in fact, 43% of hacked WordPress sites were fully updated at the time of the attack. I build custom solutions using modern "Headless" architectures (like Astro). This means your website has no exposed database or admin panel for hackers to target. It makes your digital hub virtually unhackable, protecting both your business reputation and your customers' data.
						</div>
					</details>

					<details class="group bg-white border-2 border-black shadow-[5px_5px_0_0_#000] sm:shadow-[8px_8px_0_0_#000] hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-200">
						<summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-5 sm:p-8 font-black uppercase text-[17px] sm:text-[22px] cursor-pointer outline-none hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors list-none">
							<span class="pr-4 leading-tight">Can my website automate my bookings or support?</span>
							<div class="faq-plus flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 border-4 border-black bg-surface flex items-center justify-center group-hover:bg-primary group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
								<Plus className="w-8 h-8" strokeWidth={3} />
							</div>
						</summary>
						<div class="faq-content p-5 sm:p-8 pt-0 text-[16px] sm:text-[18px] text-textSecondary font-[600] border-t-4 border-black bg-bgMain leading-relaxed">
							Yes. A modern website shouldn't just be a digital brochure; it should act as your best employee. I can integrate "Agentic AI"—intelligent digital assistants that work 24/7. Unlike simple chatbots, these AI agents can autonomously qualify leads, book appointments directly into your calendar, answer specific policy questions, and resolve basic customer service issues. This kind of integration can save you and your team up to 40 hours of administrative work per month, allowing you to focus on delivering your actual services.
						</div>
					</details>
				</div>
			</div>


		</div>
	</div>
</section>
